{
  "text": "The materials required for screening (induction script, response booklet, slide and scoring procedure) are available for download at https://osf.io/wujk8/. An induction and suggestion script was adapted from the WSGC [CITATION_1] . Participants recorded their responses in a booklet adapted from the WSGC. This contained subjective responses on a scale from 0 to 5. There were two versions of the booklet used. The second booklet differed from the first only in the addition of anchoring labels at each end of the scale used to record each subjective response. Anchoring labels were added to the second version of the booklet to reduce the possibility of erroneous responses to the subjective scale items. These restate the instructions provided in the text. For example, for Item 2, 'Moving hands together', participants are provided with the following instruction:",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "39219065"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "39219065": {
      "title": "Waterloo-Stanford group scale of hypnotic susceptibility, form C: manual and response booklet",
      "abstract": "Abstract The manual and response booklet for the Waterloo-Stanford Group Scale of Hypnotic Susceptibility, Form C (WSGC) is presented. The WSGC is a group adaptation of the individually administered Stanford Hypnotic Susceptibility Scale, Form C (SHSS:C)."
    }
  }
}